<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF206-952-306  </DOCNO><DOCID>06 952 306.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Jan 16 1989 v6 n2 p25(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Package offers specialized graphics. (Advanced Graphics SoftwareInc's SlideWrite Plus 3.0 presentation graphics software) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Picarille, Lisa.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Advanced Graphics Software Inc's $445 SlideWrite Plus 3.0presentation graphics software includes over 100 enhancements.andP;  Itoffers increased support for laser printers, new camera technologyand a greater variety of software and hardware fonts.andP;  Support forHP LaserJet or PostScript-compatible printers is included.andO;Sixteen raster-image fonts in software and 30 downloadable andcartridge fonts are included, all of which are accessiblesimultaneously.andP;  Greek and regular plotters can be mixed forplotting complex equations.andP;  There are now 12 graph typesavailable and there is a greater choice of line types and widths.andO;Registered users of previous versions of the program can upgradeto version 3.0 for $95.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Advanced Graphics Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   SlideWrite Plus 3.0 (Computer graphics software) (design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Presentation SoftwareEnhancements.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Lisa PicarilleandM;Advanced Graphics Software Inc. is expected this week to announce a newversion of its presentation-graphics software that includes more than 100enhancements, according to Larry Daniele, the firm's vice president ofresearch and development.andM;Version 3.0 of Advanced Graphics' SlideWrite Plus offers users increasedsupport for laser printers, new camera technology and a greater variety ofsoftware and hardware fonts, along with additional graph types, he added.andM;Users will have a choice of outputting their graphics to the Hewlett-PackardCo.andP;  LaserJet or PostScript-compatible printers.andP;  Version 3.0 will alsodirectly support high-quality graphics cameras, so that third-party driversare no longer required.andP;  In addition, SlideWrite Plus version 3.0 continuesto support dot-matrix printers and plotters and gives users the option ofhaving their graphics sent to slide-making service bureaus, Daniele said.andM;Version 3.0 also includes 16 raster-image fonts in software and 30downloadable and cartridge fonts, all of which are accessible simultaneously.andO;Photos, logos and supplementary images in .TIFF and .PCX file formats can beimported to and sized in an existing chart or graph.andM;Advanced graphing features in the $445 program allow users to mix Greek andregular characters for plotting complex equations.andP;  Error bars, six differentcurve fits and up to 4,000 data points can be graphed in the latest version.andM;Users agreed that the inclusion of Greek characters makes SlideWrite Plusversion 3.0 superior to Software Publishing Corp.'s Harvard Graphics forplotting and graphing scientific data.andM;''Harvard is strictly for business data,'' according to a user of graphicssoftware with the U.S.andP;  Department of Agriculture.andP;  ''It is not the programto use if you're presenting scientific data, but SlideWrite Plus clearlyunderstands the need for including scientific symbols.''andM;SlideWrite Plus version 3.0 has more graph types available -- up from four to12 -- and additional types of lines are now supported, offering users abroader choice of line types and widths to generate bold lines for reportsand slides, Daniele said.andM;Registered users of the program, which is available now, can upgrade toversion 3.0 for $95.andM;Advanced Graphics Software, of Sunnyvale, Calif., can be reached at (408)749-8620.andO;</TEXT></DOC>